Vox has entered into a strategic partnership with the Activate Group to expand its Internet of Things (IoT) offering, the company announced. The ICT provider said it will leverage the Yodiwo platform, which aims to support the fast, secure, and smooth development and deployment of large-scale IoT solutions. “Working with Activate will enable us to provide an even more enhanced solutions offering built on quick development principles to rapidly meet customer needs across industry sectors,” said Vox cloud executive head Craig Freer. “Using Yodiwo, we will be able to design and develop bespoke IoT customer applications within days instead of weeks,” Freer added. Vox also announced that it has expanded its software development team with dedicated IoT specialists.